==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Remotion
<hw>Re*mo"tion</hw> <pr>(r?-m?"sh?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>remotio</ets>. See <er>Remove</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act
of removing; removal.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This <qex>remotion</qex> of the duke and her⟦br⟧
Is practice only.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The state of being remote; remoteness.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The whitish gleam [of the stars] was the mask conferred by the
enormity of their <qex>remotion</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>De
Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Remould</ent>⟦br⟧
